Alembic migrations for NoYou.

The database URL and ORM metadata are read from the application at runtime
(see env.py): alembic.ini leaves sqlalchemy.url blank and env.py injects
app.core.config.settings.database_url, with target_metadata = Base.metadata.

Common commands (run from backend/ with the venv active):

    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
    alembic upgrade head
    alembic downgrade -1
    alembic current
    alembic history

render_as_batch=True is enabled so ALTER operations also work on SQLite.
See ../../DEPLOYMENT.md ("Database migrations (Alembic)") for the deploy flow.
